"Of course sir." Came FRACTYL's quick reply. "However there were a
tremendous variety of reptiles in the area. I can send you the
location and perhaps it can be physically investigated?"

All around the Predacons the number of birds in the air were
increasing, their calls echoing on the winds.

CYCLONUS looked at HYDRAS, "Sir, short of burning down the whole
place, do you have any suggestions as to how we are to get rid of all
these beasts?" There was the definite look of distaste in CYCLONUS'
face as he looked around. As far as anyone could see there were dead
dinosaurs of all sorts.

Mercifully the sun was beginning to set around them, which of course
meant that the nighttime scavengers were beginning to make themselves
heard as well as the sounds of ancient breeds of canines could be
heard howling in the distance as and glowing eyes could be seen even
closer.
